The folks at POV are asking for everyones comments concerning the impact of their funding crunch on the interactive portion of this web site.<br><br>
Not being shy, I decided to create a thread to encourage comments in support of what I believe is perhaps one of the most profound expressions of the power of the internet to constructively stimilate debate, education, and free expression. <br><br>
The very first post on this site was by POV:<br><br>
&gt;&quot;YOUR COMMENTS PLEASE<br>
           Mon Nov 4 20:47:37 US/Eastern 1996 <br><br>
Re: Vietnam is a new endeavor for POV Interactive and we are<br>
excited about the possibilities for bringing people together to share stories, thoughts, and experiences in this space.<br><br>
We will be continuing to develop this site over time. <br><br>
We would like to hear your comments and suggestions. <br><br>
           -- stories@pov.org (POV Interactive)&quot;&lt;<br><br>
In just under five months, this site has stimulated more interest and excitement than anything else now posted on the POV web site. I know. I just checked. In fact, the Vietnam Protest thread has far more postings than all other interactive POV sites combined.<br><br>
What a return on investment!<br><br>
As a side benefit, PBS has received concrete evidence of a realization of its goals of public education in ways it perhaps it did not consider. Not only did Professor Grivetti's students win here, but there was a young lady from South Africa, many Veitnam Veterans, protestors, families, friends, a psychologist here and there, and the formerly uninformed, all of whom won here, too.<br><br>
The richness of the educational, emotional, and factual tapestry woven here is, I believe, unsurpassed anywhere.<br><br>
The Supreme Court recently characterized the Internet as a truly global conversation. Well, PBS, here it is. Look closely before you leap too far and retreat back into the innards of the television set. You should be as proud of this site in ways as honored and enthusiastic as are its participants. We all are truly winning here.<br>
     
